cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.SY

The paper proposes a new optimization algorithm inspired by animal behavior, which is a common theme in the field of swarm intelligence. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also mentions the use of real-world applications such as the traveling salesman problem and ambulance routing, indicating a focus on practical problem-solving, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses the performance of the algorithm in comparison to other state-of-the-art algorithms, suggesting a focus on machine learning and optimization, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
